cles by embracing a culture of safety, investing in staff education, and engaging patients and families in their care.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-86_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-87_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-88_">Fostering a culture of safety and continuous improvement</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-90_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Creating a culture that prioritises safety and continuous improvement is essential for the success of clinical governance. This involves leadership commitment, transparency, and an organisational mindset that views mistakes as opportunities for learning and growth.</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-92_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/young-woman-doctor-taking-care-of-patient-from-res-2023-11-27-05-34-56-utc.jpg?v=1709051101" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/young-woman-doctor-taking-care-of-patient-from-res-2023-11-27-05-34-56-utc.jpg?v=1709051101 1536w" width="1856" height="1237" alt="Mitigate Risks with Advanced Clinical Risk Management E-learning - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mitigate Risks with Advanced Clinical Risk Management E-learning - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-93_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-94_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  halfpoint via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-96_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-97_"><img src="h